hosp <- read_csv("C:/Users/student/Documents/hospp.csv")

#Sample in 10,000 observations from over 100,000
hd <- hosp[sample(nrow(hosp), 10000),]

#Create a log of tot variable, add 1 so that a tot of 0 does not turn into infinity
hd <- hd %>% 
  mutate(logtot = log(hd$tot) + 1)

#Get rid of some more variables that have a lot of missing values
hd <- hd %>% 
  select(-payfix, -preopday, -obs_hour, -nicu_day, -pay_ub92)

#Replace missing length of stay values with the median
hd %>% 
  map(~sum(is.na(.)))

#Create another variable, date, that combines the year and month for additional graphical analysis
monthfrac <- h %>% 
  mutate(monfrac = moa/12)
h <- monthfrac %>% 
  mutate(date = yoa + monfrac)

#Find out medians of each numeric variable per year and month
mdate <- h %>% 
  group_by(date) %>% 
  summarise_if(is.numeric,~median(., na.rm = TRUE))

#Graph of log tot per date
datelogtot <- ggplot(mdate, aes(x = date, y = logtot)) + geom_point()
datelogtot

#Create new variable, admtypechar that changes the numbers of admtype to be the reason for type of admission into hospital
h <- h %>% 
  mutate(admtypechar = if_else(admtype == 1, "Emergency", if_else(admtype == 2, "Urgent", if_else(admtype == 3, "Electric", if_else(admtype == 4, "Newborn", if_else(admtype == 5, "Court Committal or Trauma", "NA"))))))

#Calculate median values per admission type
totperadmtype <- h %>% 
  group_by(admtypechar) %>% 
  summarise_if(is.numeric, ~median(.,na.rm = 1))
totperadmtype

GLM for tot

h.glmdata <- h %>% 
  select_if(., is.numeric)

h.glm <- h.glmdata %>% 
  select(-logtot)

split <- createDataPartition(h.glm$tot, p = 0.7, list = F)
h.training <- h.glm[split,]
h.testing <- h.glm[-split,]

mod1 <- glm(tot ~ ., data = h.training, family = Gamma(link = "log"))
mod1.pred <- predict.glm(mod1, h.testing, type = "response")
sum(h.testing$tot)/sum(mod1.pred, na.rm = TRUE)
## [1] 0.9908066

Decision tree for binary log(tot)

mlt <- median(h$logtot)
h <- h %>% 
  mutate(binlogtot = if_else(logtot <= mlt, 0, 1))
h$binlogtot <- as.factor(h$binlogtot)

h.treedata <- h %>% 
  select(-tot, -logtot, -asource, -icu, -dispub92, -payer, -ccu, -raceethn)
splitIndex <- createDataPartition(h.treedata$binlogtot, p = .70, list = FALSE)
train <- h.treedata[splitIndex,]
test <- h.treedata[-splitIndex,]

for(i in 1:6) {
mytree <- rpart(binlogtot ~ ., data = train, method = "class", control = rpart.control(maxdepth = i))
pred <- predict(mytree, test, type = "class")
cm= confusionMatrix(data = pred, reference = test$binlogtot, positive = "1")
print(cm$overall[[1]])}
## [1] 0.6840123
## [1] 0.6829853
## [1] 0.7648066
## [1] 0.767203
## [1] 0.7812393
## [1] 0.7812393

Random Forest for binary log(tot)

accuracy = c()
for (i in 1:8) {for (w in 3:8){
mod2 <- ranger(binlogtot ~ ., data = train, mtry = i, num.trees = w, splitrule = "gini")
mod2.pred <- predict(mod2, test)$predictions
mod2.cm <- confusionMatrix(mod2.pred, test$binlogtot, positive = "1")
accuracy <- append(accuracy, cm$overall[[1]], length(accuracy))}}

max(array(accuracy, dim = c(8,6)))
## [1] 0.7812393

Linear Discriminant Analysis for binary log(tot)

mod3 <- train(binlogtot ~ ., train, method = "lda2")

mod3.pred <- predict(mod3, test)

mod3.cm$overall[[1]]
